71. calathis, here ‘goblets' or ‘flagons' (not ·baskets‚’ as in 2. 46). So in G. 3. 4cz it probably means ‘milk-cans.' Ariusia, a town and district of Chios. Chian wine was in great repute; hence the term nectar, denoting something very choice. In G. 2. 98 Virgil calls the wine of Phanae in the same island the ‘king’ of wines.
